{
  "texts": [
    "When the first basin (blue) is filled, the MD simulation is allowed to traverse high transition barrier and explore the red basin.",
    "Once the red basin is also filled, the accumulated biases are summed, enabling estimation of the negative free energy landscape (represented by the grey dashed line).",
    "C Replica exchange method: several replicas are simulated in parallel at different temperatures.",
    "In regular intervals exchange in temperatures/configurations between replicas is attempted.",
    "This exchange is allowed only when Metropolis criterion is satisfied (Liao 2020)."
  ]
}